    public class ClassNode
extends InstanceDeclarationNode
    DeclarationNode extension that represents the declaration of a class node type. See decodeStatement(TreeNode, String, Location, boolean, boolean) for more details on what correct inputs look like.

      • decodeStatement

        public static ClassNode decodeStatement(TreeNode parent,
                        java.lang.String statement,
                        Location location,
                        boolean require,
                        boolean scope)
        Decode the given statement into a ClassNode, if possible. If it is not possible, this method returns null.

        Example inputs include:
        • public class ClassName
        • private static class ClassName
        • public abstract class ClassName
        Parameters:
        parent - The parent of the current statement.
        statement - The statement to translate into a ClassNode if possible.
        location - The location of the statement in the source code.
        require - Whether or not to throw an error if anything goes wrong.
        scope - Whether or not the given statement is the beginning of a scope.
        Returns:
        The generated node, if it was possible to translated it into a ClassNode.

                Bounds bounds,
                int numWords,
                java.lang.String leftDelimiter,

                TreeNode.ExtraData extra)
        Description copied from class: TreeNode
        Method that is to be overridden. Whenever the iterateWords(String) method is called, this method will be called with the specific word and the number (order) the word came in the statement.

        Parameters:

        wordNumber - The index of the word on a word-by-word basis.
        bounds - The bounds of the word that was found.
